    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10468757>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1–13. Aamunops kalebi sp. nov. 1. Male prosoma, dorsal; 3. Same, lateral; 5. Same, ventral; 7. Same, anterior. 2. Male opisthosoma, dorsal; 4. Same, lateral; 6. Same, ventral; 8. Female prosoma, dorsal; 9. Same, ventral. 10. Male leg I, prolateral; 11. Same, leg II; 12. Female leg I, prolateral. 13. Same, leg II. Scale bars 1–9: 1.00 mm; 10–13: 0.50 mm. Abbreviations: ca, crista; gl, gladius." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10468757/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10468761>
    dc:description "FIGURES 14–20. Aamunops kalebi sp. nov. 14. Male palp, prolateral; 15. Same (inset showing detail of apical portion), ventral; 16. Same, retrolateral; 17. Copulatory bulb, prolateral; 18. Same, retrolateral; 19. Internal genitalia (digested and cleared), dorsal; 20. Same, dorsal. Scale bars 14–18: 0.20 mm; 19–20: 0.25 mm. Abbreviations: ap, anterior plate; arb, anteromedian receptacle base; Cb, cymbium; cs, chemosensory setae patch; e, embolus; ep, embolar process; hp, hyaline process; ip, posterior invagination; mp, median projection; pb, prolateral brush; pp, posterior plate; psb, pair of sclerotized bars; sac, membranous sac-like structure; t, tracheal trunk; Ti, tibia." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10468761/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10468763>
    dc:description "FIGURES 21–32. Aamunops kalebi sp. nov. 21. Male palp bulb, prolateral; 22. Same, apical; 23. Same, retrolateral; 24. Detail of embolus, hyaline process, and embolar process, prolateral; 25. Same, apical; 26. Same, ventral; 27. Male prolateral tibial brush; 28. Male leg I, prolateral; 29. Same, leg II; 30. Female leg I, prolateral; 31. Same, leg II; 32. Female palp (inset showing prolateral tibial brush), prolateral. Scale bars 21–23, 28–32: 0.20 mm.Abbreviations: aj, adesmatic joins; ca, crista; e, embolus; ep, embolar process; gl, gladius; hp, hyaline process; Mt, metatarsus; pb, prolateral brush." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10468763/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10468769>
    dc:description "FIGURE 49–51. 49–50. Roddenberryus spock Sánchez-Ruiz & Bonaldo, 2023, live specimens (photographs by Humberto Bahena). 51. Known distribution of Aamunops species." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10468769/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

